    <title>Women's Advancement contributor: Ndoni Mcunu</title>
    <description>Ndoni Mcunu holds a Master’s in Science (MSc) in Applied Environmental Science. She is currently pursuing a PhD (Doctor of Philosophy) at the Global Change Institute at Witwatersrand University, with the supervision of Professor Robert Scholes. Ndoni is the founder &amp;amp; member of Black Women in Science (BWIS) a registered non-profit organization which aims at providing scientific and research skills for science students and graduates.
</description>
